00:49:14.040 --> 00:49:17.340
&gt;&gt; My Name is Tracy K.
Smith, and I'm delighted

00:49:17.340 --> 00:49:20.820
to congratulate you on having
been selected this year's

00:49:20.820 --> 00:49:23.180
National Student Poets.

00:49:23.180 --> 00:49:26.870
It speaks to the commitment
that you've already demonstrated

00:49:26.870 --> 00:49:31.740
to poetry as an art form,
and as a way of life.

00:49:31.740 --> 00:49:37.300
As I see it, poems teach us new
ways of looking at the world.

00:49:37.300 --> 00:49:41.270
They give us new terms for
describing the many active

00:49:41.270 --> 00:49:44.790
and powerful feelings
that we live with.

00:49:44.790 --> 00:49:47.480
And they also allow
us to listen closely

00:49:47.480 --> 00:49:50.060
to other people's
voices and their stories.

00:49:50.060 --> 00:49:53.300
I think all of that is
indispensable to a full life.

00:49:53.300 --> 00:49:57.640
And I'm thrilled that over the
next year you will be able to go

00:49:57.640 --> 00:50:00.990
into your communities, doing
this with other people,

00:50:00.990 --> 00:50:04.040
talking about why
poetry matters to you.

00:50:04.040 --> 00:50:06.830
That's what I've been doing over
the last year as Poet Laureate

00:50:06.830 --> 00:50:10.770
and it's been one of the most
rewarding acts of my life

00:50:10.770 --> 00:50:14.560
as an artist, and a person
to go into communities

00:50:14.560 --> 00:50:17.240
with people I don't know,
people I may never see again,

00:50:17.240 --> 00:50:21.180
and feel like we actually have
something meaningful to say

00:50:21.180 --> 00:50:24.310
to one another through
the vehicle of poetry.

00:50:24.310 --> 00:50:26.530
I'm sorry I'm not there with
you tonight, I'm actually

00:50:26.530 --> 00:50:30.460
in Alaska talking
poetry with new friends.

00:50:30.460 --> 00:50:32.260
But I'm excited to
join you tomorrow

00:50:32.260 --> 00:50:34.510
and celebrate your
accomplishments.

00:50:34.510 --> 00:50:39.510
